Mail Plane Fleet Being Organized 
China's Posts and Telecommunications Ministry is organizing its own
fleet of mail planes, which is to take off in October.
Two postal air routes will be opened by then, one starting from
Beijing, via Wuhan to Guangzhou, and the other from Beijing via
Shanghai to Xiamen, according to the latest issue of the "People's
Posts and Telecommunications".
Preparations for the founding of the China Postal Air Route Company are
going smoothly.
The first batch of three special "Yun 8" planes will be delivered in
August. The central postal airport is located in Liangxiang, southwest
of Beijing, the paper said.
